50|$|Plionarctos is an extinct genus {{of mammals}} {{of the family}} <b>Ursidae</b> (bears) endemic to North America and Europe during Miocene through Pleistocene, living from ~10.3—3.3 Mya, {{existing}} for about 7 million years.|$|E
50|$|Ursus is a genus in {{the family}} <b>Ursidae</b> (bears) that {{includes}} the widely distributed brown bears, the polar bear, and black bears. The name {{is derived from the}} Latin ursus, meaning bear.|$|E
